==Japanese==

===Etymology===
The copula {{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} is thought to be a contracted version of {{m|ja|である|であります|tr=dearimasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|ある|alt2=あります|tr2=arimasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; however, there are other possibilities, namely {{m|ja|でござる|でございます|tr=degozaimasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|ござる|alt2=ございます|tr2=gozaimasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; {{m|ja|でする|tr=desuru}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|する|tr2=suru|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; {{m|ja|でおわす|tr=deowasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|おわす|tr2=owasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; and {{m|ja|でそうろう|tr=desourou}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|そうろう|tr2=sourou|lang=ja|nocat=1}}.

===Verb===
{{ja-verb|h|rom=desu|hidx=てす'}}
# expresses politeness toward the listener
# polite [[copula]]

====Usage notes====
Perfective form is でした, volitional でしょう, conjunctive でして. Other forms are not used. Replaces [[だ]] ([[da#Japanese|da]]) in cases of nouns and adjectives which it is used with, e.g. 犬だ becomes 犬です and [[綺麗]]だ becomes [[綺麗]]です. Similarly, でしょう replaces だろう and でして replaces で.

です attaches as is to adjectives used without だ, e.g. [[美しい]] becomes [[美しい]]です and 美しかった becomes 美しかったです. Forms such as 美しいでした and 美しいでして are nonstandard. For the forms ないです and なかったです there are synonyms ありません and ありませんでした.

